# High-Speed, High-Fluency Clinical Translation (Few-Shot)

To address the latency and "unnatural" translation quality, this plan simplifies the execution to a single-pass model call while significantly increasing output quality through **Few-Shot Clinical Prompting**.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Single-Pass Execution**: We will remove the "Refinement" pass to cut translation latency by ~50%.
> **Few-Shot Examples**: I will provide 3-5 real-world medical question examples in the prompt to "train" the LLM contextually on its output tone.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. [MODIFY] [translation_utils.py](file:///e:/Medathon/translation_utils.py)
Update the `TranslationService` to:

- **Remove `_refine_translation`**: Move all "quality" logic into the primary prompt to save time.
- **Few-Shot Context**: Inject a `FEW_SHOT_EXAMPLES` block into every translation prompt. This teaches the model the exact "Doctor-Patient" tone required for Tamil and Hindi.
- **Hard-Coded Corrections**: Create a dictionary of "Clunky vs. Fluent" phrases to instantly swap common mistranslations without using the LLM.
- **Regex Punctuation Cleanup**: Keep the `؟` -> `?` and other character cleaning but do it programmatically after the single LLM pass.

### 2. [MODIFY] [orchestrator.py](file:///e:/Medathon/orchestrator.py)
Ensure that we are not translating the same static strings repeatedly (e.g., headers like "1. What is happening?"). I will implement a small **Translation Cache** for identical strings.

